cs.NI, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.SY, cs.RO 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) as it deals with indoor positioning using access points. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it uses a particle filter for tracking. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as it deals with location sequences and similarity-based approaches. It could also be categorized under cs.SY (Systems and Control) as it involves dead reckoning for tracking. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.RO (Robotics) as it deals with tracking a mobile user in an indoor environment.
